    <tags>bff-api, services, refactoring, architecture-binding</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Tags include 'bff-api'; refactors interface + retires placeholder methods on a production surface; FR-25 binding; FULL per task-execute Step 0.5.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>4-P</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Rename `IChatDataverseRepository` → `IChatAuditRepository`; retire the 5 placeholder `Task.CompletedTask` no-op methods (per spec FR-25 + architecture §7.2 + §11.4). The Cosmos `audit` container is the sole compliance reader going forward — `sprk_aichatmessage` becomes a pure write-target (audit trail). Per architecture §11.2 strategy, retired read methods become extension methods that throw `NotSupportedException` to preserve binary compat through a stabilization window.
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform BFF developer with refactoring expertise. Familiar with R6 chat persistence + ADR-013 facade boundary.</role>

  <goal>
    Interface renamed; old reader methods either deleted OR throw `NotSupportedException`; `ChatDataverseRepository.cs` write methods preserved for compliance audit trail; integration test confirms audit writes still succeed; grep confirms zero remaining read consumers of the retired methods.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per spec FR-25 + architecture §7.2 + §11.4. `ChatDataverseRepository` shipped with 5 `Task.CompletedTask` no-op methods + a 10K-character cap on message reads — broken placeholder code that was never wired to real consumers. Per Owner decision (CLAUDE.md Decisions table, 2026-06-21), retire the read surface entirely; Cosmos `audit` (`AuditLogService`) is the canonical reader for compliance. The repository's WRITE methods remain (audit trail). Per architecture §11.2, throwing `NotSupportedException` from the retired read methods preserves binary compat through the stabilization window.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/IChatDataverseRepository.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/ChatDataverseRepository.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/ChatSessionManager.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/ChatHistoryManager.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Infrastructure/DI/AnalysisServicesModule.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Infrastructure/DI/AiModule.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Audit/AuditLogService.cs</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec FR-25">5 `Task.CompletedTask` no-ops removed; `GetMessagesAsync` deleted OR throws `NotSupportedException` for stabilization window; integration test confirms audit writes succeed; grep confirms zero read consumers remain.</constraint>
    <constraint source="architecture §7.2">`sprk_aichatmessage` becomes write-only audit role; Cosmos `audit` is sole reader.</constraint>
    <constraint source="architecture §11.2">Old read methods become extension methods that throw `NotSupportedException` — preserves binary compat through stabilization window.</constraint>
    <constraint source="architecture §11.4">Document `sprk_aichatmessage` as pure write-target; remove all reader code paths in chat; preserve writes for compliance audit trail.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">Stays inside `Services/Ai/` boundary; no CRUD-code direct-injection regressions.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-015">Tier-2 audit content allowed per ADR-015 amendment (hash, IDs, tool names); preserve existing tier compliance.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">Per-task BFF publish-size measurement; expect minor delta only.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Test update obligation (CLAUDE.md §10) — modify tests covering this repo + DI registration.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/architecture/stateful-chat-architecture.md</file>
