      <file>.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read `IChatDataverseRepository.cs` + `ChatDataverseRepository.cs` to inventory: (a) the 5 `Task.CompletedTask` no-op methods; (b) any remaining write methods (preserve); (c) all callers via grep.</step>
    <step order="2">Grep `IChatDataverseRepository` across `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` — identify all references including DI module registrations and constructor injections.</step>
    <step order="3">Rename interface file → `IChatAuditRepository.cs` (audit-only contract). Update class name to match. Keep write methods (audit trail).</step>
    <step order="4">Decide per-method: delete OR retain-as-throwing-NotSupportedException. Per architecture §11.2 strategy, prefer extension methods that throw — preserves binary compat. Apply consistently.</step>
    <step order="5">Update all DI registrations: `AnalysisServicesModule.cs`, `AiModule.cs` — register `IChatAuditRepository` → `ChatAuditRepository` mapping.</step>
    <step order="6">Update all consumers (`ChatSessionManager.cs`, `ChatHistoryManager.cs`) — verify they only call WRITE methods or are themselves refactored to call `AuditLogService` for reads.</step>
    <step order="7">Update unit + integration tests under `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Chat/` — rename test classes; assert NotSupportedException on retired methods; assert writes still succeed.</step>
    <step order="8">Run `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` + tests — must pass.</step>
    <step order="9">Grep prove: `grep -rn "IChatDataverseRepository" src/` returns zero hits (or only legacy comments).</step>
    <step order="10">Measure BFF publish size; report delta.</step>
    <step order="11">code-review + adr-check (Step 9.5 quality gates).</step>
    <step order="12">Update TASK-INDEX.md: task 101 → ✅; update current-task.md.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="Read">Repository + interface + DI + consumer files</tool>
    <tool name="Grep">Enumerate references to old interface name; verify zero remain after rename</tool>
    <tool name="Edit">Rename + retire methods + update DI + update consumers + update tests</tool>
    <tool name="Bash">dotnet build / test / publish</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
